Privacy Policy for Code Snippet Saver

Effective Date: [9/22/24]

1. Introduction

This Privacy Policy explains how the Code Snippet Saver extension collects, uses, and protects your information. By using this extension, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.

2. Information We Collect

User-Provided Data: When you save code snippets, we collect the following information:
Code snippets you enter.
Associated metadata, such as programming language and topic tags.
3. How We Use Your Information

The information we collect is used to:

Allow you to save and organize your code snippets.
Improve the functionality and user experience of the extension.
4. Data Storage

All data is securely stored using Chrome's storage API. We do not store any personally identifiable information (PII) or sensitive data.

5. Data Security

We take the security of your data seriously. While we strive to protect your information, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure. We cannot guarantee absolute security.

6. User Rights

You have the right to:

Access the snippets you have saved.
Delete any saved snippets from your storage at any time.
7. Third-Party Sharing

We do not share your data with third parties except as required by law.

8. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page.

9. Contact Us

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at [hekramul333@gmail.com].
